                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-11-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 16, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Hay, replying to Mr. Conger’s telegram of the 14th instant, states that we
                    favor securing foreign rights at treaty ports by adequate foreign concession,
                    either as an international settlement or separate for the interested nations;
                    but forcible appropriation, under claim of conquest, conflicts with the declared
                    purposes of the powers and disturbs their harmonious action. Mr. Conger’s
                    protest is approved. We think the matter should be conventionally adjusted as
                    part of the general arrangement, in which the rights of the United States of
                    America should be reserved to an impartial share.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
